<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-07-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-07-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="60" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d60">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 2413/141.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-07-20"><hi rend="italic">July 20,
                                1908</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Edict to-day gives T’ang Shao-yi rank of president of a board and
                            appoints him special envoy to the United States to express the thanks of
                            China for the action of the United States in reference to the indemnity.
                            Will probably leave early in November.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Rockhill.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>